BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF OHIO:
Section 1. That section 4507.09 of the Revised Code be 5
amended to read as follows: 6
Sec. 4507.09. (A)(1) Except as provided in division (B) of 7
this section, every driver's license issued to a resident of 8
this state expires on the birthday of the applicant in the 9
fourth or eighth year after the date it is issued, based on the 10
period of renewal requested by the applicant. A resident who is 11
sixty-five years of age or older may only apply for a driver's 12
license that expires on the birthday of the applicant in the 13
fourth year after the date it is issued. In no event shall any 14
license be issued for a period longer than eight years and 15
ninety days. 16
Subject to the requirements of section 4507.12 of the 17
Revised Code, every driver's license issued to a resident is 18
renewable at any time prior to its expiration. 19
(2) A driver's license issued to a temporary resident 20

